include ../mixins/container

mixin Compel(values)
  +container(values)
    p When <strong>you persuade someone to do something</strong>, envision your approach and roll. If you...
    ul
      li Charm, pacify, barter, or convince: Roll +heart (add +2 if you share a bond).
      li Threaten or incite: Roll +iron.
      li Lie or swindle: Roll +shadow.
      li Flaunting or boasting: Roll +wealth or +supply.
    p On a <strong>strong hit</strong>, theyâ€™ll do what you want or share what they know. Take +2 momentum. If you use this exchange to <em>Gather Information</em>, make that move now and add +2.
    p On a <strong>weak hit</strong>, as above, but they ask something of you in return; envision what they want. If you are making this move to persuade a conditional companion, suffer -1 loyalty instead.
    p On a <strong>miss</strong>, they refuse or make a demand which costs you greatly. <em>Pay the Price</em>; if you are making this move by interacting with a conditional companion, suffer -1 loyalty instead.